18 SECTION 3.(a) Article 29A of Chapter 115C of the General Statutes reads as
19 rewritten:
20 "Article 29A.
21 "Policy Prohibiting Use Of Tobacco Products and Hemp-Derived Consumable Products.
22 "§ 115C-407. Policy prohibiting tobacco product and hemp-derived consumable product
23 use in school buildings, grounds, and at school-sponsored events.
24 (a) Not later than August 1, 2008, local boards of education Governing bodies of public
25 school units shall adopt, implement, and enforce adopt a written policy prohibiting at all times
26 the use of any tobacco product or hemp-derived consumable product by any person in school
27 buildings, in school facilities, on school campuses, and in or on any other school property owned
28 or operated by the local school administrative public school unit. The policy shall further prohibit
29 the use of all tobacco products and hemp-derived consumable products by persons attending a
30 school-sponsored event at a location not listed in this subsection when in the presence of students
31 or school personnel or in an area where smoking is otherwise prohibited by law.
32 (b) The policy shall include at least all of the following elements:
33 (1) Adequate notice to students, parents, the public, and school personnel of the
34 policy.
35 (2) Posting of signs prohibiting at all times the use of tobacco products and
36 hemp-derived consumable products by any person in and on school property.
37 (3) Requirements that school personnel enforce the policy.
38 (c) The policy may permit tobacco products to be included in instructional or research
39 activities in public school buildings if the activity is conducted or supervised by the faculty
40 member overseeing the instruction or research and the activity does not include smoking,
41 chewing, or otherwise ingesting the tobacco product.
42 (d) The North Carolina Health and Wellness Trust Fund Commission Tobacco
43 Prevention and Control Branch shall work with local boards of education governing bodies of
44 public school units to provide assistance with the implementation of this policy including
45 providing information regarding smoking cessation and prevention resources. Nothing in this
46 section, G.S. 143-595 through G.S. 143-601, or any other section prohibits a local board of
47 education governing body of a public school unit from adopting and enforcing a more restrictive
48 policy on the use of tobacco products or hemp-derived consumable products in school buildings,
49 in school facilities, on school campuses, or at school-related or school-sponsored events, and in
50 or on other school property.
51 (e) For the purposes of this section, the following definitions apply:
